</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/padding-left.html")</para><para>An element&amp;apos;s padding area is the space between its content and its border.</para><blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><para><strong>Note:</strong> The <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding">padding</see> property can be used to set paddings on all four sides of an element with a single declaration.</para></blockquote>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_box_model/Introduction_to_the_CSS_box_model">Introduction to the CSS basic box model</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-top">padding-top</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-right">padding-right</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-bottom">padding-bottom</see> and the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding">padding</see> shorthand<br/>-The mapped logical properties: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-block-start">padding-block-start</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-block-end">padding-block-end</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-inline-start">padding-inline-start</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-inline-end">padding-inline-end</see> and the shorthands <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-block">padding-block</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/padding-inline">padding-inline</see><br/></para>
